# CODEOWNERS — review routing for sensitive paths.
#
# Scoped narrowly to .github/workflows/** to surface workflow changes as
# code-owner-required review in the PR UI, without adding review noise to
# unrelated paths.
#
# Why this path specifically: a downstream privileged self-hosted runner
# (homelab UNK-231 Phase 4) executes the contents of these workflow files
# as root on the deploy host via mounted docker socket + incus binary.
# The deploy step is gated by `github.event_name == 'push' && github.ref
# == 'refs/heads/main' && github.actor == '<owner>'` on the runner side;
# this CODEOWNERS entry adds a complementary review-surface signal so
# workflow-touching PRs cannot land unnoticed inside a larger diff.

/.github/workflows/         @junkovich
